HEADWORD: Horology
<hw>Ho*rol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Horologe</er>.]</ety> <def>The science of measuring time, or the
principles and art of constructing instruments for measuring and
indicating portions of time, as clocks, watches, dials, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

